The illusion spell I posted before was more like a shapeshift abilitiy, were you could change your shape to look like the targeted mob/enemy player/realmmate.  I believe I was suggesting it in the matter line back then.  <P>If you could LOOK and smell like a troll until you started to cast a spell, you wouldn't need an instant - you could waltz up into a group of mids and then cast mez.  To balance the power you have to resume your regular shape for 5 seconds before starting to cast.<P>At different spec levels you would gain additional targets.<P>10th Spec level: Humanoid shapes of the same relative size<BR>20th Spec level: Non-humanoid shapes of the same relative size<BR>30th Spec level: Humanoid shapes of any size<BR>40th Spec level: non-humanoid shapes of any size<P>So at Spec level 30 you could look like a troll invader/defender.<P>At spec level 40 you could look like a bloodletter.<P>If this was made into illusions in mind, they could add resists where someone will not believe the illusion.<P>Also you only look like the targeted mob, you don't get any of the abilities.<P>Maybe in DAoC2  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Malachai Mindbender<BR>Sorcerer of Avalon<BR>Guinivere<BR> <IMG SRC="http://www.brainwaresolutions.com/sorcerer.gif"> 
