What's wrong with it, is that it is something "new" & they would have to code it...ain't gonna happen.<BR>----------------------------------------<P>If the developers were open to new ideas, I'd love to see this idea, which kind of goes along the same lines as the whole "illusions" thing.  I've mentioned this before, but what I would LOVE to have would be an Instant, temporary stealth SPELL.<BR>Here's how it might play out.<BR>- You cast a mez & it gets resisted/purged, etc & you have 5 trolls running straight for you...sound familiar?<BR>- The first troll gets to you & gives you a whack for 500+ damage.  Death is imminent...well maybe not...<BR>- Hit Vanish Spell<BR>- POOF, Sorcerer is consumed by a cloud of smoke.  Targeting is cleared for any enemies who had Sorcerer targetted.<BR>- Sorcerer has 10 seconds of Invisibility to get to safety.  After 10 seconds, Sorcerer comes back into view.<BR>- Being that it is a "Mind Twisting" spell, it would not be affected by Rogue/Stealth skills like high stealth level or See Hidden.<BR>- Casting a spell would bring Sorcerer back into vision.<BR>- 10min timer.<P>Considering the short duration and the timer, this would prevent it from being abused as an offensive weapon, but the Instant Cast & Target Clearing would be an awesome defensive boost to help us out of some sticky situations & increase our survivablitiy.<P>Possible Level Options:<BR>- Level 10 = 3 Seconds<BR>- Level 20 = 6 Seconds<BR>- Level 30 = 9 Seconds<BR>- Level 40 = 12 Seconds<BR>- Level 50 = 15 Seconds<P>This would give level 20-30 Mind people some nice, much needed defensive options, but would also give the level 40-50 Mind people some possible sneak attack options for investing all those points & giving up their offense.  Plus, I just dig the whole "disappearing in a cloud of smoke" idea...would be a blast just to play with it.<P>--------------------<P><B>Quote 7/2/02 - i3ullseye, Sorcerer Team Lead: Actually no, i am not 'your' representative. this has been